import React from 'react';
import {Icon} from 'semantic-ui-react';

export default function HandleDropdown(props) {
  const dataValue = props.dataValue;
    switch (dataValue) {
    case 'Priority':
            return (<>
  <option value="Low">Low</option>
  <option value="Normal">Normal</option>
  <option value="High">High</option>
  <option value="Safety">Safety</option> </>
)
    case 'Status':
           return (<>
  <option value="Low">Low</option>
  <option value="Normal">Normal</option>
  <option value="High">High</option>
  <option value="Safety">Safety</option> </>
)
    case 'Category':
           return <Icon name='orange circle'size='large'/>
     case 'Asset':
            return <Icon name='blue circle'size='large'/>
    case 'Description':
           return <Icon name='red circle'size='large'/>
               
               default:
                return <Icon name='red circle'size='large'/>
        
}
}

const status = [
  { text: 'Raised'},
  {text: 'Raised and Assigned'},
  { text: 'In Progress'},
  {text: 'On Hold'},
    {text: 'Completed'},
   
]
const category = [
  { text: 'None'},
  {text: 'Equipment'},
  { text: 'Paddock'},
  {text: 'Fuel Tank'},
    {text: 'Silo'},
    {text: 'Livestock'},
   
]
